This tiddler collects all of the //simple// WikiText markup — the structural and
inline formatting — leaving out widgets, macros, variables, filters, pragmas and
other programmatic constructs (those have their own demo tiddlers).

! Headings

! Heading level 1
!! Heading level 2
!!! Heading level 3
!!!! Heading level 4
!!!!! Heading level 5
!!!!!! Heading level 6

A heading can carry one or more CSS classes:

!.myclass.another Heading with classes

! Paragraphs and line breaks

A normal paragraph is one or more lines of text. A blank line separates one
block from the next. A soft line break inside a paragraph is joined into the
same paragraph when rendered.

Force a run of hard line breaks with triple double-quotes:

"""
Line one
Line two stays on its own line
Line three too
"""

