Three or more dashes alone on a line draw a horizontal rule:

---

! Inline formatting

''Bold'' text, //italic// text, __underline__ text, ~~strikethrough~~ text.

Super^^script^^ and sub,,script,, text.

``Inline code`` and @@highlighted@@ text.

Combinations nest: ''//bold italic//'', //''italic bold''//, __//underlined
italic//__ and ~~//struck italic//~~.

! Inline code variants

A single backtick pair for `inline code`, and a double backtick pair when the
code itself must contain a literal backtick:

``code with a ` backtick inside``

Inline code is literal — markup inside it is not interpreted: `''not bold''` and
`//not italic//`.

! Styled and classed inline spans

@@.tc-big-green-button A span with a CSS class@@
@@color:red;A span with an inline CSS colour@@
@@background-color:yellow;color:black;Multiple CSS declarations@@
@@color:blue;.myclass CSS and class together (styles must precede classes)@@

! Dashes and special characters

Dashes: an en-dash -- and an em-dash --- written inline.

HTML entities: &amp; &copy; &mdash; &rarr; &hellip; &#x2192; &#160; &nbsp;.

There is no backslash-escape in WikiText: a `\` is a literal character. To show
wiki characters literally, use inline code or HTML entities, e.g. &#47;&#47; for
two slashes or &lbrace;&lbrace; for two braces.

